For all devices:\
\
There may be times when a FireWire audio device will not show up after a reboot. This version of the driver is more stringent about the responses and values returned from the device. If there are any serious errors or extended timeouts from the device during enumeration, the driver will stop querying the device and fail the device enumeration. If this happens a message will be printed out in the system.log file. If your device fails to enumerate often, you may need to modify your devices firmware to the latest version from your silicon vendor or modify some of your existing commands to respond in a timely fashion with the correct values.\
\
For some devices:\
\
The are a small number of devices that do not work well with the new streaming engine. We have included an exception list in the info.plist of the AppleFWAudio kext to revert the devices in the exception list to the old streaming engine. This is a temporary work around until we resolve the issues with the silicon vendors on what is preventing there devices from working correctly with the new streaming engine. If you find your device is not working with this version of the driver, you can add your device's vendorID and modelID to the info.Plist of the AppleFWAudio.kext and restart your computer. Make sure you 'Touch' the directory so that the kexts will be re-scaned and re-added to the kext cache during the next boot.\
